Why CERN-OHL-S v2
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SlopDrive-32 incorporates source ported from fray-d/OSSM-Lite
(https://github.com/fray-d/OSSM-Lite), which is distributed under CERN-OHL-S v2.
CERN-OHL-S is strongly reciprocal: any Product or Source that conveys a Covered
Work derived from it must be made Available under CERN-OHL-S v2. Accordingly the
whole of SlopDrive-32 is licensed under CERN-OHL-S v2.

Ported from fray-d/OSSM-Lite (CERN-OHL-S v2):
  - The "Advanced Penetration" pattern algorithm: per-direction min/max depth,
    in/out speed and in/out acceleration, the master-speed feel curve, and the
    cyclic per-stroke modifier math (ramp-to-min / at-min / ramp-to-max /
    at-max, amplitude, offset).
      -> include/motion/AdvancedPattern.h, src/motion/AdvancedPattern.cpp
  - The twelve factory presets (Simple, Teasing, Pounding, Robo, Half'n'half,
    Deeper, Insist, Jackhammer, Progressive, Mid, Knot 75%, Knot 50%), decoded
    from OSSM-Lite's preset strings.
      -> webui/src/features/pattern.js (AP_PRESETS)

The BLE characteristic plumbing, on-device display UI, and NVS preset string
codecs from OSSM-Lite were not used; only the motion numerics were ported.

